    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the roster, carrying an elite 81.88 score. Facing Houser, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a potent combination of a 16% park factor boost and the #1 lineup spot, making him our highest-upside play for both R and SB production. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.80) and **Marcell Ozuna** (66.28) follow closely as primary sources for RBI; **Marcell Ozuna** specifically draws a 10% efficiency boost due to favorable winds, providing a solid anchor in the middle of our lineup against Taillon. Meanwhile, **Miguel Vargas** remains a strong play at 64.07, capitalizing on a favorable wind outlook and a lead-off assignment that should maximize his exposure to scoring opportunities.\n\nWhile the core is set, we are exercising caution with **Kyle Tucker** (57.87) and **Andy Pages** (43.59) as they draw the difficult assignment of deGrom. Their scores are suppressed by the elite SP_xERA, though **Kyle Tucker** remains a mandatory start due to his high base projection and potential to steal points even against high-end velocity. The most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo** (54.50); while he benefits from the same park factors as **Gunnar Henderson**, his projected spot at the bottom of the order and lower base efficiency compared to **Jorge Polanco** (58.28) kept him on the pine. **Jackson Merrill** (58.20) warrants a close watch; despite a strong projection, he faces a 39% rain risk that could lead to an early exit or shortened game, potentially neutralizing his value if the weather turns.",
